message.content:
1. Total WOMAC scores improved in all groups at early follow-up (3 months) compared to baseline.
2. The HA1 group had a reduction of 44.79% in total WOMAC scores at early follow-up compared to baseline.
3. The HA2 group had a reduction of 24.02% in total WOMAC scores at early follow-up compared to baseline.
4. The HA3 group had a reduction of 40.38% in total WOMAC scores at early follow-up compared to baseline.
5. The PRP group had a reduction of 39.77% in total WOMAC scores at early follow-up compared to baseline.
6. The control group had a reduction of 27.64% in total WOMAC scores at early follow-up compared to baseline.
7. There was a statistically significant difference (p=0.002) in the reduction of total WOMAC scores between the HA1 and HA2 groups at early follow-up.
